      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782640769739,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Distributed email system",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Distributed email system",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "To2vPe0V_3n_26niDz-qw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 225.4796905517578,
      "y": 227.14804077148438,
      "width": 768.0594482421875,
      "height": 1725,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bFn",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1085548398,
      "version": 978,
      "versionNonce": 410874674,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782641452572,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Questions?\n\nq. system like gmail?\nyes\n\nq. scale?\n1 billion users\n\nq. imp features?\nsend email\nreceive email\nwith attachment\nfetch all emails by folder ( all, inbox, spam, trash etc)\nfilter emails by read and unread\nsearch emails by subject, text, sent by etc\nemail chain ( optional)\nanti spam and anti virus scans\n\nq. attachment?\nyes\n\nq. traditioanl emails worked on SMTP and IMAP, do we use them or API based\nyour choice\n\nFunctional req:\nsend email\nreceive email\nwith attachment\nfetch all emails by folder ( all, inbox, spam, trash etc)\nfilter emails by read and unread\nsearch emails by subject, text, sent by etc\nemail chain ( optional)\nanti spam and anti virus scans\n\n\nNFR:\nHigh availability : 99.99\nDurability \nlow latency\nReliability\nScalability\n\nBack of the envelop calc:\n\n1 billion users\nDAU : 100 m users\nsend 10 emails a day\neach email = 50 kb\n\nstorage\n100m * 10 * 50 kb\n= 10^9 * 50 kb\n= 50tb per day\n365 days * 10 years\n= 50 * 365 * 10 tb\n= 1825 * 100 tb\n= 182.5 PB\n\ntraffic\nsend = 10\nreceive = 40 emails\n\ncalls APIs 50 times a day\n= 100m * 50\n= 5 b per day\nrps \n= 5b / 10^5\n= 5 10^9 / 10^5\n= 5 * 10^4 = 50000 rps",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Questions?\n\nq. system like gmail?\nyes\n\nq. scale?\n1 billion users\n\nq. imp features?\nsend email\nreceive email\nwith attachment\nfetch all emails by folder ( all, inbox, spam, trash etc)\nfilter emails by read and unread\nsearch emails by subject, text, sent by etc\nemail chain ( optional)\nanti spam and anti virus scans\n\nq. attachment?\nyes\n\nq. traditioanl emails worked on SMTP and IMAP, do we use them or API based\nyour choice\n\nFunctional req:\nsend email\nreceive email\nwith attachment\nfetch all emails by folder ( all, inbox, spam, trash etc)\nfilter emails by read and unread\nsearch emails by subject, text, sent by etc\nemail chain ( optional)\nanti spam and anti virus scans\n\n\nNFR:\nHigh availability : 99.99\nDurability \nlow latency\nReliability\nScalability\n\nBack of the envelop calc:\n\n1 billion users\nDAU : 100 m users\nsend 10 emails a day\neach email = 50 kb\n\nstorage\n100m * 10 * 50 kb\n= 10^9 * 50 kb\n= 50tb per day\n365 days * 10 years\n= 50 * 365 * 10 tb\n= 1825 * 100 tb\n= 182.5 PB\n\ntraffic\nsend = 10\nreceive = 40 emails\n\ncalls APIs 50 times a day\n= 100m * 50\n= 5 b per day\nrps \n= 5b / 10^5\n= 5 10^9 / 10^5\n= 5 * 10^4 = 50000 rps",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
